OL,7,FThe student, who cannot be named, took
OL,8,Flegal action against Michaela
OL,9,FCommunity School in Brent, claiming
OL,10,Fthe policy was discriminatory and
OL,11,F"uniquely" affected her faith due to
OL,12,Fits ritualised nature.
OL,14,FShe argued the school's stance on
OL,15,Fprayer ` one of the five pillars of
OL,16,FIslam ` unlawfully breached her right
OL,17,Fto religious freedom and was "the kind
OL,18,Fof discrimination which makes
OL,19,Freligious minorities feel alienated
OL,20,Ffrom society".
